r himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Weston Esq. Lord of Weston and Hindedale was born in 1396, in Uckfield, Sussex, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Weston Esq, Lord of Hindedale, was 30 and his mother, Joan de Hindedale, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Joan de Wintershell."},"et":{"1396–":"1396–Surnud","1396–Male":"1396–Surnud","1396–Female":"1396–Surnud","1421–Male":"1421–Surnud","1366–Male":"1366–Surnud","1371–Female":"1371–Surnud","1421":"1421","1366":"1366","1396":"1396","1371":"1371","Hendall Manor, Uckfield, Sussex, England":"Uckfield, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1396–":"1396–Kuollut","1396–Male":"1396–Kuollut","1396–Female":"1396–Kuollut","1421–Male":"1421–Kuollut","1366–Male":"1366–Kuollut","1371–Female":"1371–Kuollut","1421":"1421","1366":"1366","1396":"1396","1371":"1371","Hendall Manor, Uckfield, Sussex, England":"Uckfield, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1396–":"1396–Décédé","1396–Male":"1396–Décédé","1396–Female":"1396–Décédée","1421–Male":"1421–Décédé","1366–Male":"1366–Décédé","1371–Female":"1371–Décédée","1421":"1421","1366":"1366","1396":"1396","1371":"1371","Hendall Manor, Uckfield, Sussex, England":"Uckfield, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Weston Esq. Lord of Weston and Hindedale est né en 1396, à Uckfield, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, William Weston Esq, Lord of Hindedale, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Joan de Hindedale, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan de Wintershell."},"de":{"1396–":"1396–Verstorben","1396–Male":"1396–Verstorben","1396–Female":"1396–Verstorben","1421–Male":"142